#note having ENCAGED blocked was painful, but I actually still have a shot if I can make a better play here. CONGEED at A6 scores 3 more vital points, and also leaves a spot for the H at 15A. Counterintuitively, it seems like I would want to block that, but by leaving the H spot on the board, I give myself a chance to draw the H and outrun Henry (I often draw other good outs). CONGEED wins with a draw of EH, GH, HN and HS out of the bag, and also requires him to find stuff like HELVING and ELVISH in a couple of other scenarios. Holding the A after CONGEED might also put more pressure by letting me draw out-plays at N8. With the actual pool of HI, I would've lost by just two points with optimal play.
